<H2><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C"><B>EUCHARISTIC PRAYER II (Offering, Intercession, Doxology)</B></FONT></H2>
<H3><PRE>

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P. Therefore, as we celebrate
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                       Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   the memorial of his Death and Resurrection,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   we offer you, Lord, the bread of life
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   and the chalice of salvation,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   giving thanks that you have held us worthy
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   to be in your presence and minister to you.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Humbly, we pray,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Bm
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   that, partaking of the Body and Blood of Christ,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Am                                       Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   we may be gathered into one by the Holy Spirit.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Remember, Lord, your Church
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                          Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   spread throughout the world,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   and bring her to the fullness of charity,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   together with N., our Pope,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Am                  Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   and N., our Bishop, and all the clergy.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Remember also our brothers and sisters
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Bm
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   who have fallen asleep
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   in the hope of the resurrection
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Am                            Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   and all who have died in your mercy:
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   G                     Bm            Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   welcome them into the light of your face.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   G                        Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Have mercy on us all, we pray:
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   that with the Blessed Virgin Mary, Mother of God,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   with Blessed Joseph her spouse,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   with the blessed Apostles and all the Saints
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   who have pleased you throughout the ages,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   we may merit to be coheirs to eternal life,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">             G             Bm
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   and may praise and glorify you
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                 A           Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   through your Son, Jesus Christ.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Through him, and with him, and in him,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">     Bm
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   O God, Almighty Father,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   in the unity of the Holy Spirit,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                           Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   all glory and honor is yours
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   forever and ever.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Bm    A     Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. Amen, Amen, Amen.

</PRE></H3>
